]}]}]},{"id":"167","parent":"0","text":"CONSIDERACIONES GERIATRICAS","guid":"FO_h4t0ZRD-XbmY2E2WNlg","children":[{"id":"168","parent":"167","text":"HTA secundaria en AM","guid":"-wxX2tF7TpKUfIx1EY09Gw","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"Mas frecuente que en jovenes si HTA resistente o de reciente empeoramiento","guid":"091hIRGbTk6CTpK5lT0Ncg","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"Estenosis renal ateromatosa → causa mas frecuente en >65 anos con HTA y enf. vascular","guid":"dq_tBOziTMK9H8FHdsLXpQ","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"168","text":"SAHOS sub-diagnosticado en AM (presentacion atipica: insomnio en vez de somnolencia)","guid":"Qf1X-HX2QMWtep0tlVoduw","children":[]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"167","text":"Hiperaldosteronismo en AM → considerar ante hipokalemia en polifarmacia","guid":"s3J9I_eiSFyp9tNFMqddrA","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"167","text":"Feocromocitoma → puede presentarse con inestabilidad PA no controlada o en incidentaloma","guid":"MWbgOA4_The7QuqCXUq0vQ","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"167","text":"Hipercortisolismo → fuente exogena (corticoides prescriptos) muy comun en AM","guid":"1WI4jBmxRkqlS8RU-A6Xdg","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"167","text":"Estudio de HTA 2a en AM → individualizar segun esperanza de vida y beneficio terapeutico","guid":"aRI2cHBTSC6pZvtLsMbj3g","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"167","text":"Coartacion de aorta → rara en AM (generalmente ya diagnosticada en jovenes)","guid":"4qlP93J4TSu3VQBPDQqISw","children":[]}]},{"id":"177","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIEN","guid":"XKwa6VkoRNKQj_iJge510A","children":[{"id":"178","parent":"177","text":"→ HTA (manejo general) (Cardiologia)","guid":"S-6xzSt8QNa16AZH-AMZCw","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"177","text":"→ Crisis HTA (Cardiologia)","guid":"zIc0tUaPQVmsCqeA-L94cw","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"177","text":"→ Farmacologia cardiovascular (Farmacologia)","guid":"1EOYMXN3SZiXEmhmwh4kBA","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"177","text":"→ Farmacos antiHTA (Cardiologia)","guid":"MWFkXR1XSkGk7fRGLfghTA","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"177","text":"→ ERC y HTA (Nefrologia)","guid":"9u7I092KQ7afdQe67CyLrQ","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"177","text":"→ Incidentaloma adrenal (Endocrinologia)","guid":"6I-giSrmStORJcbgp8xQ3A","children":[]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"0","text":"PERLAS CLINICAS","guid":"wnBXpGJQTU64dBNgKVHA5A","children":[{"id":"185","parent":"184","text":"HTA resistente → screening de HTA 2a OBLIGATORIO (estenosis renal, aldosteronismo, SAHOS)","guid":"skiTrZjFT4efYm6IbmZHOg","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"184","text":"HIPOKALEMIA espontanea en hipertenso → hiperaldosteronismo hasta demostrar lo contrario","guid":"dkR29hzqSESPIspbegQ_SQ","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"184","text":"IECA/ARA2 que duplican creatinina al inicio → estenosis bilateral o renal critica","guid":"fQ0LVOCkSbitgAAcRghgAQ","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"184","text":"Feocromocitoma: NUNCA beta-bloqueo sin alfa previo → puede precipitar crisis HTA grave","guid":"IiKwERlATI28LHWQzKoZLg","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"184","text":"SAHOS → unica causa de HTA 2a con \"non-dipping\" nocturno en MAPA como clave diagnostica","guid":"NDQFHsimThG7KazV8X3i6A","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"184","text":"Displasia fibromuscular → PTCA renal (sin stent) → excelente respuesta en jovenes","guid":"bM1zakjXSIO4uAlhcA1B7Q","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"184","text":"Hipercortisolismo exogeno → lo mas comun en clinica; SIEMPRE preguntar por corticoides","guid":"r-8dbxJERbKQPRW1QiefbQ","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"184","text":"Crisis HTA paroxistica (cefalalgia+palpitaciones+diaforesis) → feocromocitoma hasta descarte","guid":"GMx3GGulQx6WJVLkEDD43w","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"184","text":"REFERENCIAS","guid":"rol_RaIbTL6aOYxr8LE4ug","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"1. Williams B, et al. 2018 ESC/ESH Guidelines for management of arterial hypertension. 